        title: `Bachelor of Arts in History <br /> <span class="font-normal">University of Florida</span> <br /> <span class="text-sm font-normal">2020 - 2024</span>`,
        icon: 'tabler:school',
      },
    ]}
    classes={{ container: 'max-w-3xl' }}
  />-->

  <!-- Content Widget **************** -->

  <Content
    id="porfolio"
    title="Building Spectacular Sites"
    subtitle="Feel free to check out some of my best projects below. You'll find a some small business websites, a landing page, and a full-stack web app."
    isReversed
    items={[
      {
        title: 'Description:',
        description:
          'Two fast, SEO optimized websites for small businesses. One is Gainesville Web Design, my own web design business, and the other is Catalyst Consulting, a consulting firm.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Role:',
        description:
          'For Catalyst Consulting, I was hired to assist in a rebrand. I led the full design and development of the site, including implementing Decap CMS, optimizing for SEO, and ensuring full responsiveness. For Gainesville Web Design, I designed and developed it to show off my web development services.',
      },
    ]}
    image={{
      src: smallBusinessImage,
      alt: 'Mockups of Gainesville Web Design and Catalyst Consultings homepage',
      layout: "fill",
    }}
    callToAction={{
      target: '_blank',
      text: 'Go to the project',
      icon: 'tabler:chevron-right',
      href: 'https://www.gnvwebdesign.com/',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white sm:text-3xl mb-2">
       Small Business Websites <br /><span class="text-2xl">GNV Web Design & Catalyst Consulting</span>
      </h3>
    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="bg">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-transparent"></div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <!-- Content Widget **************** -->

  <Content
    isReversed
    isAfterContent={true}
    items={[
      {
        title: 'Description:',
        description:
          'Built in Webflow to advertise an upcoming church conference for The Father’s House. The site is fully responsive and features interactive animations.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Role:',
        description: `Hired via Upwork to develop this site from a Figma design. Finished the full project, including responsiveness across all devices, in about a week.`,
      },
    ]}
    image={{
      src: landingPageImage,
      alt: 'A mockup of the mobile site for TFH Church Conference',
      layout: "fill",
    }}
    callToAction={{
      target: '_blank',
      text: 'Go to the project',
      icon: 'tabler:chevron-right',
      href: 'https://tfhconference.com/',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white sm:text-3xl mb-2">
        Landing Page <br /><span class="text-2xl">TFH Church Conference</span>
      </h3>
    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="bg">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-transparent"></div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <!-- Content Widget **************** -->

  <Content
    isReversed
    isAfterContent={true}
    items={[
      {
        title: 'Description:',
        description: `A site containing the stats from every college baseball player since 2020. My first solo full-stack project, I went through many iterations on the architecture of the site until ending with a React.js frontend with Firebase handling the backend. Stats are collected using the college-baseball Python library.`,
      },
      {
        title: 'Role:',
        description: `Led the design and development of both the frontend and backend. The frontend is simple compared to most projects I've done, I used the MaterialUI component library. I wanted the focus to be on the players and their stats.`,
      },
    ]}
    image={{
      src: webAppImage,
      alt: 'A picture of College Baseball Stats',
      layout: "fill",
    }}
    callToAction={{
      target: '_blank',
      text: 'Go to the project',
      icon: 'tabler:chevron-right',
      href: '#',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="content">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-white sm:text-3xl mb-2">
        Full-Stack Web App <br /><span class="text-2xl">College Baseball Stats</span>
      </h3>
    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="bg">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-transparent"></div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <!-- Testimonials Widget *********** -->

  <Testimonials
    title="Client testimonials"
    subtitle="Discover what clients have to say about their experiences working with me."
    testimonials={[
      {
        testimonial: `To all of my entrepreneur friends and peers, and anyone looking to make the leap to a professional website and polished online presence - I can’t recommend Jonah and his crew enough!`,
        name: 'Ryan Bowman',
        job: 'Founder, Catalyst Consulting',
      },
      {
        testimonial: `Jonah was super personable and worked with me and my companies marketing budget. We appreciate him & his help on our site.`,
        name: 'Kallie Smith',
        job: 'Watford Engineering',
      },
      {
        testimonial: `Jonah was very responsive and really listened to what I wanted with my website. I will definitely work with again.`,
        name: 'Maureen Fitzsimmons',
        job: 'Tampa Bay Luxury AV',
      },
      {
        testimonial: `Jonah was quick to respond and understood what I needed help with right away. He was thorough with his work and very detail oriented. I would definitely work with Jonah again.`,
        name: 'Jason McCord',
        job: 'Founder, Hometrics',
      },
      {
        testimonial: `Jonah was outstanding! I needed a second set of eyes and an expert with website/web page design prowess and Jonah fit the bill. I will be using Jonah for all website design changes moving forward.`,
        name: 'Frank Greco',
        job: 'MyFamilyPlan',
      },
      {
        testimonial: `Jonah was extremely responsive and technically proficient. I've already hired him for a second project, and plan to do more in the future!`,
        name: 'David Peterson',
        job: 'Bethesda Dog Walking',
      },
    ]}
  />

